                <h1>CVE</h1>
                <h5>Waseeb Aman Kaths</h5>
                <p>YCHR Engaged 300 Community Members To Counter The Influence Of VE Groups And Dissemination Of Extremist Propaganda By Forming 30 Waseeb Amn Kaths (WAKs-Community Peace Assembly) In Target Villages Of Bosan Town, District Multan, By Reviving Local Dispute Resolution Structures. Each Village Had A 15 Member WAK Comprising Of; Community Elders, Teachers, Farmers, Minorities, Local Councilors, And Representatives From Different Faiths And Sects.
                These 20 WAKs Are Equipped And Capacitated And Serve As A Common Place Where People From All Segments Of Society Sit Together Regularly (Weekly Or Bi-Weekly Basis)To Address Local Issues Including Extremism Within Their Communities, And Develop Strategies To Resolve Conflicts With Consensus.Ninety (90) Social Action Projects Both Budgeted And Self-Initiatives, Were Implemented By The 30 WAKs. More Than 23000 Beneficiaries Attended The SAPs On Regular Basis To 
                Address VE And Other Local Issues,And To Develop Strategies To Resolve Conflicts With Consensus.</p>
                <h5>Establishing Awami Baithak To Enhance Community Cohesiveness</h5>
                <p>YCHR Established Six Awami Baithaks In District Muzaffargarh Equipped With A Computer, Major Daily Newspapers And Informative Materials On The Topics Of Human Rights, Womens’ Rights, Child Rights, Labor Rights, Interfaith Harmony And Peace.The Coordinators (One Male And One Female) For Each Awami Baithak Were Provided With Training On Social Mobilization,Community Organization,Behavior Change Communication,Advocacy,And Computer Literacy.Weekly Debates,
                   Monthly Forums, Movie Nights,Cultural Shows Were The Main Activities Conducted At These Awami Baithaks.The Purpose Of The Intervention Was To Develop Community Cohesion And Avenues For Freedom Of Expression Through Dialogue, Discussion, Education And Cultural Entertainment Organized Through The Awami Baithak.</p>
                <h1>Non-Formal Education</h1>
                <h5>Home School Education Program</h5>
                <p>In Lahore Aimed To Raise The Educational Level Among The Target Communities And Generate Job Opportunities For The Girls And Educate Them About Human And Women Rights; Youth Commission For Human Rights- Center For Research And Training Initiated Home School Education Project From March 15,2016 With The Support Of Small Grants And Ambassador’s Fund Program. This Is A Multi- Grade Learning Approach And Designed To Address The Needs Of Out Of School Children
                   In Two Underdeveloped Districts Of Punjab (Lahore & Muzaffargarh). A Baseline Field Survey Conducted By The Organization In Underdeveloped And Marginalized Areas Of Muzaffargarh And Lahore Highlighted Alarming Facts Regarding The Status Of Out Of School Children.Under The Umbrella Of Home School Education Project, YCHR Established 20 Home Schools 15 In District Muzaffargarh And 05 In District Lahore.</p>
                <h1>Capacity Building Trainings</h1>
                <h5>Political Education Program</h5>
                <p>Focused On Building The Capacity Of The Elected Representatives To Performance Of Their Duties. Trainings Were Conducted For All The Elected Councilors And Members Of Citizen Community Boards From District Lahore With The Support Of Devolution Trust For Community Empowerment. It Was Followed By Training And Establishment Of Monitoring Committees For District And Tehsil Councils In District Sheikhupura,Funded By CIDA-DSP, Which Was Preceded By A Successful
                   Baseline Study Which Set The Tone For The Capacity Building Activities.</p>
                <h1>Environmental Sanitation</h1>  
                <h5>Environment Education Program</h5> 
                <p>Was Aimed At Raising Environmental Awareness Among Schoolchildren From Low-Income Localities</p>
                <h5>Community Health & Sanitation Programs</h5>
                <p>In Lahore, Kasur, Sialkot And Bahawalpur Were Implemented In Low-Income Localities To Improve Health And Sanitation Conditions And Benefited More Than 5000 Household.</p>
                <h5>Solid Waste Management Programs</h5>
                <p>In Kotlakhpat, Qadri Colony, Walled City And Township, Lahore, Are Evidence Of Our Commitment To Improving Environmental Conditions.</p>
